claim.claim-text:
1. A method of delivering an antimicrobial composition to the proximal end of a transdermal catheter, the method comprising:
a) providing a transdermal catheter implanted within a patient, the transdermal catheter having a proximal end located outside of the patient and a distal end located at least partially within a blood vessel of the patient, the catheter comprising:
i) a hub located at the proximal end of the catheter,
ii) exterior threads on the proximal end of the hub, and
iii) an interior channel in the hub leading from an opening at the proximal end of the catheter to a lumen in the catheter, wherein at least a portion of the interior channel has a tapered interior surface;

b) providing an antimicrobial composition delivery device for insertion into the proximal opening of the catheter, the antimicrobial composition delivery device comprising:
i) a retaining ring comprising threads configured to engage the exterior threads on the catheter hub;
ii) a soluble non-liquid antimicrobial composition located on the threads of the retaining ring; and
iii) a tapered member configured for insertion into the catheter hub, the tapered member configured to substantially seal the proximal end of the catheter;

c) injecting a liquid lock solution into the transdermal catheter such that at least the proximal end of the transdermal catheter is substantially filled with the lock solution;
d) applying a clamp across the proximal end of the catheter, the clamp substantially preventing the flow of fluids across the clamped portion of the catheter; and
after applying the clamp, insertion of the tapered member of the antimicrobial delivery device into the hub located at the proximal end of the catheter so as to displace liquid lock solution from the interior of the catheter hub to the exterior of the catheter hub such that at least a portion of the antimicrobial composition on the threads of the retaining ring is transferred to the threads of the hub.

23. A method of delivering an antimicrobial composition into the proximal end of a transdermal catheter, the method comprising:
a) providing a transdermal catheter implanted within a patient, the transdermal catheter having a proximal end located outside of the patient and a distal end located at least partially within a blood vessel of the patient, the catheter comprising:
i) a hub located at the proximal end of the catheter,
ii) exterior threads on the proximal end of the hub, and
iii) an interior channel in the hub leading from an opening at the proximal end of the catheter to a lumen in the catheter, wherein at least a portion of the interior channel has a tapered interior surface;

b) providing an antimicrobial composition delivery device for insertion into the proximal opening of the catheter, the antimicrobial composition delivery device comprising:
i) a retaining ring comprising threads configured to engage the exterior threads on the catheter hub;
ii) a soluble non-liquid antimicrobial composition located on the threads of the retaining ring;
iii) a tapered member configured for insertion into the catheter hub, the tapered member configured to substantially seal the proximal end of the catheter; and
iv) an elongate member located on the antimicrobial deliver device, the elongate member configured for insertion into the hub of the transdermal catheter along with the tapered member;

c) injecting a liquid lock solution into the transdermal catheter such that at least the proximal end of the transdermal catheter is substantially filled with the lock solution;
d) clamping the transdermal catheter; and
e) insertion of the tapered member and elongate member of the antimicrobial delivery device into the hub located at the proximal end of the clamped catheter so as to displace the liquid lock solution from the interior of the catheter hub to the exterior of the catheter hub such that at least a portion of the antimicrobial composition on the threads of the retaining ring is transferred to the threads of the hub;
wherein upon insertion of the elongate member into the hub, the elongate member displaces a portion of the liquid lock solution from the interior of the hub to the exterior of the hub.

29. A method of delivering an antimicrobial composition into the proximal end of a transdermal catheter, the method comprising:
a) providing a transdermal hemodialysis catheter implanted within a patient, the transdermal hemodialysis catheter having a proximal end located outside of the patient and a distal end located at least partially within a blood vessel of the patient, the catheter comprising:
i) a hub located at the proximal end of the catheter,
ii) exterior threads on the proximal end of the hub, and
iii) an interior channel in the hub leading from an opening at the proximal end of the catheter to a lumen in the catheter, wherein at least a portion of the interior channel has a tapered interior surface;

b) providing an antimicrobial composition delivery device for insertion into the proximal opening of the catheter, the antimicrobial composition delivery device comprising:
i) a retaining ring comprising threads configured to engage the exterior threads on the catheter hub;
ii) a soluble chlorhexidine composition located on the threads of the retaining ring; and
iii) a tapered member configured for insertion into the catheter hub, the tapered member configured to substantially seal the proximal end of the catheter; and
iv) an elongate member located on the antimicrobial deliver device, the elongate member configured for insertion into the hub of the transdermal catheter along with the tapered member;

c) injecting a liquid lock solution into the transdermal catheter such that at least the proximal end of the transdermal catheter is substantially filled with the lock solution; wherein injecting the liquid lock solution comprises:
i) using a syringe to inject the liquid lock solution, the syringe partially inserted into the catheter hub;
ii) clamping the transdermal catheter;
iii) upon removing the syringe from the hub, the syringe tip leaves a unfilled void at the proximal end of the hub, and
iv) wherein the tapered member and elongate member have a volume greater than the volume of the unfilled void;

e) insertion of the tapered member and elongate member of the antimicrobial delivery device into the hub located at the proximal end of the clamped catheter so as to displace liquid lock solution from the interior of the catheter hub to the exterior of the catheter hub such that at least a portion of the chlorhexidine composition on the threads of the retaining ring is transferred to the threads of the hub;
f) formation of a precipitate of the chlorhexidine composition in the hub of the catheter;
g) evaporation of at least a portion of the displaced liquid lock solution so as to form a deposit of non-dissolved antimicrobial composition on the threads of the hub; and
h) exposing the hub to moisture sufficient to redissolve at least a portion of the antimicrobial composition located on the threads of the hub.
